# Overnight agent constraints

- Work on feature branches only (`overnight/*` or `agent/*`). Never push directly to `main`.
- Do not merge pull requests. Do not force-push.
- Run `mvn test` before opening a PR; all 78 JUnit tests must pass.
- Change at most 5 files per run unless the user explicitly widens scope.
- Do not modify `.github/workflows/`, secrets, credentials, or dependency major versions without explicit approval.
- Do not run destructive commands (`rm -rf`, `git reset --hard`, `git push --force`).
- If blocked (ambiguous spec, failing environment, flaky tests), stop and leave a clear summary instead of guessing.
